ute fact. I've played on Rallos Zek from day 1. I know, and knew then, if I was killed i could lose something. It's my choice to either bag my belongings, or wear full armor/gear and make myself more efficient. If there is no risk, then the excitement, the reason we play on Rallos in the first place, has been taken away. Who cares if you die... you don't lose anything. Coin? Give me a break. No one carries much coin around on Rallos anyway. You loose some plat, big deal. I've lost 250pp during PvP before. Made no difference. It's only coin afterall. <BR>  <BR> With looting in place, EverQuest actually supports alternate quests. Meaning, since we can be looted, we all try to equip ourselves in nodrop gear. nodrop equipment on Rallos Zek is a huge thing. Take looting away, and you have taken reason away to even bother with nodrop, except the planes gear of course... which is desired for stats. On the blue-servers, nodrop is an inconvenience... on Rallos, it is a neccessity. <BR>  <BR> What needs to be done is a reworking of the PvP system that is in place now. Verant obviously isn't into true PvP. They should be. There's going to be a lot of cancelled accounts when the new games come out, and Verant is still lagging behind. True, the minority of EQ players are into PvP... but is that because people dont like PvP... or is it because Verants idea of PvP is skewed. Verant has made big changes to EQ, that have totally effected PvP, and it seems as if they have not bothered to think about the consequences. <BR>  <BR> The worst nerf on PvP to date, imo, is the jboots / cheeta / sow / selos not cancelling Root / Snare / etc. Mainly JBoots. They were a huge weapon in PvP. Not only did it allow a way out of being bound to the ground, but it made melee classes much more effective in PvP combat. A lot of complaints about PvP have been issued by melee classes, and with one nerf, Verant made melee'ers even worse. Then, to top it all off, Verant makes JBoots more rare. What should have been done, was the addition of another JBoot spawn point, maybe two. Perhaps one in MMoore, one in Kerra Isle. Allow more access to such a viable peice PvP equipment. Anyway, all that is beside the point I'm trying to make. <BR>  <BR> Basically it comes down to this: I, and a lot of players, didn't spend 1000's of hours playing a game to have the rules so drastically changed once we have reached the top. We don't pay 10$ a month for a year, play 40+ hours a week, to play under one set of rules and have them changed. <BR>  <BR> My personally suggestion is to start a new server... a PvP server with coin-only loot. Leave Rallos Zek, the original PvP server, as it is. Make your changes to the Team PvP server(s). I couldn't care less. It's already a toned-down version of Rallos Zek PvP. It's been infested with blue-server wanna-be PvPers, and their ranting and raving over being killed by their own race, looted, PvP'ed... has finally been heard by Verant. I applaud their tenacity and dilligent efforts to destroy PvP on their own servers, but I only ask that Rallos Zek is left as it is. <BR>  <BR> We all know Verant isn't interested in PvP. We all know that there were originally no plans to have a PvP server. We all know that some serious arm-twisting needed to be done to even get Rallos Zek going... but don't take it away now. <BR>  <BR> At any rate, with the current system in place now, Coin-Only loot is an insult to PvP. <BR>  <BR> xein, rz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/udreadie.showPublicProfile>DreaDie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333399>(2/12/00 5:06:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP</span><hr size=1> The big reason they impla